          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304335744-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> red Thai curry paste</strong> and your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add 600ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> [1.2L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with your<strong> creamed coconut </strong>and<strong> sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304369744-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304369744-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304369744-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304369744-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1606304369744-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken breast </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p><p>Meanwhile, trim your<strong> green beans</strong>, then chop them into thirds and set aside for later</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304381773-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304381773-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304381773-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304381773-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304381773-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> and <strong>medium egg noodles</strong></p><p>Tip: Nestle the noodles into the sauce for even cooking!</p><p>Cover with a lid and return the dish to the oven for 10-12 min further or until the noodles are tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>one-pot Thai red chicken breast noodle soup</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1606304393909-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1606304393909-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1606304393909-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1606304393909-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1606304393909-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the<strong> one-pot Thai red chicken breast noodle soup </strong>with the<strong> sliced onion </strong>and<strong> chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Tip: Watch out for the ginger halves and discard them!</p><p>Tear over your<strong> coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
